<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-02-15T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-02-15T11:00:00-05:00" n="274" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d274">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">838.51/4167: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Sparks</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-02-15T11:00:00-05:00">February 15, 1941—11
                                    a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 12:33 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>28. Legation’s telegram No. 26, February 13, 5 p.m. Enabling legislation
                            to put into effect the supplementary executive agreement was enacted and
                            promulgated yesterday.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Sparks</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>